<br>
If it's a NBG group then NBG.<br>
If your in a Greed group then all can roll on all drops.<br>
<br>
Ask what is going on before you step off and hunt.<br>
Set up the loot rules first so there is no mistake what is going to happen when the loot does drop.<br>
<br>
I have always had the mind set, that if you are spending time with me in a group, you should have a fair crack at the loot that drops. Melee, caster, hybrid, whatever.<br>
Don't get me wrong... If there was a drop that an other could use to better their character that they are playing with, in group, and they say &quot;I can use this to better the gear, spells that I have now&quot;, then Gratz to ya.  ( just my vote, it depends what the rest of group says, but I do vocalize in group that we are here to help eachother get better gear/spells if we can )<br>
When I group I try to make sure everyone in the group walks away with something.<br>
I have been known to /random on class spacific items if the group won't give it to that person, and if I win the roll, give the item to the class spacific person for that Item just to help them out. No strings attached.<br>
And yes... Cleric costs of dots and other classes with component costs should be reinburst, after group has finished with the camp.<br>
It's just considerate to do so. And good gaming.<br>
<br>
