<br>
I had yet to be in a pickup group &quot;back in the days&quot; where some dr00d didn't insist on rolling for cobalt, or a lammy or whatnot, yet the same players will insist melees not roll on parchments, which is a double standard.<br>
<br>
The bottom line is- if a drop is tradeable, or a quest item for an end result is tradeable, everyone should roll for it.  I'll only hear out exceptions for very needy players (i.e. tank is a mana sponge still wearing a few bronze pieces and tradeable drops = tank gets piece by group decision) or if the sole purpose for the group is pre-declared for a particular goal/drop.  (i.e. a group taking a druid to CoM for a jade reaver = druid loots, or group taking a tank to sewers seb specifically for a cb = tank loots clickie cobalt bracer, should it drop).<br>
<br>
A little common sense goes a long way, even if there are tards in your group.  Most exp. grind pickup groups that just so happen to get a decent, tradeable drop/toy or parchment should roll. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ganndon>ganndon</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.eqguild.net/guilds/Ganndon/Picture%2029.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Senior Member</span><br>  Posts: 623<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/9/02 10:47:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3506.topic&index=49>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Parchments</span><hr size=1> Im glad as fuck i only group with my guild <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
